# Jarwiz server environment.
# Copy this file to `.env` (same directory) — the server loads it at startup.

# ── ANTHROPIC_API_KEY ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is the one thing you need for the *full* Jarwiz experience.
#
#   • Set it, and everything runs for real through the Anthropic API — asks,
#     deep web research, Autopilot, the Thinking Machines, clustering, diagrams,
#     link-preview cleanup. Web search uses Anthropic's built-in web_search
#     tool, so this single key covers it too.
#
#   • Leave it unset, and Jarwiz still runs — in demo mode. You get scripted,
#     hand-authored stand-in output so you can explore the canvas with no key.
#     (If you happen to have the Claude Code CLI installed locally, the server
#     uses it as a keyless "sidecar" for real output instead — purely a dev
#     convenience; it is never required.)
#
# The key never leaves the server — the browser only ever sees parsed results.
# Get one at https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Port for the HTTP server. The web app's Vite dev proxy expects 3001.
PORT=3001

# ── Everything below is OPTIONAL ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Jarwiz runs fine without any of these — they only tune advanced/local bits.
# Leave them unset unless you specifically need them.

# The keyless "sidecar": if the Claude Code `claude` CLI is installed and signed
# in, the server uses it for real output when ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is not set.
# CLAUDE_CLI_PATH points at the binary if it isn't on your PATH; set
# JZ_DISABLE_SIDECAR=1 to turn the sidecar off entirely (force demo mode).
# CLAUDE_CLI_PATH=
# JZ_DISABLE_SIDECAR=

# Watched-video cards. With yt-dlp + ffmpeg on your PATH, dropping a video URL
# pulls captions AND samples real frames Jarwiz can "watch". Without them, video
# gracefully falls back to captions only — nothing breaks. Point these at the
# binaries if they aren't on your PATH.
# JZ_YTDLP_PATH=
# JZ_FFMPEG_PATH=

# PDF OCR. The bundled eng.traineddata (Tesseract) ships in the repo root, so
# scanned PDFs are read with no extra download. Override the data path only if
# you keep the traineddata elsewhere.
# TESSERACT_LANG_PATH=

# Where uploaded assets (dropped images/PDFs) are written. Defaults to a temp
# dir; set this to persist them somewhere stable.
# JARWIZ_ASSET_DIR=

# Multiplayer sync (?room=) is parked behind a flag pending security hardening.
# Leave unset. Must match the web app's VITE_JARWIZ_ENABLE_SYNC to have any effect.
# JARWIZ_ENABLE_SYNC=
